âœ… Different Ways to Use Threads in Java:
1. Extending the Thread class

class MyThread extends Thread {
    public void run() {
        System.out.println("Thread running using Thread class");
    }
}
Usage:


MyThread t = new MyThread();
t.start(); // starts a new thread
2. Implementing the Runnable interface

class MyRunnable implements Runnable {
    public void run() {
        System.out.println("Thread running using Runnable");
    }
}
Usage:


Thread t = new Thread(new MyRunnable());
t.start();
ğŸ”¸ More flexible than extending Thread (since you can extend another class).

3. Using Lambda Expression (Java 8+)

Thread t = new Thread(() -> {
    System.out.println("Thread using lambda");
});
t.start();
âœ… Clean and concise way to implement threads.

4. Using ExecutorService (Thread Pooling)

ExecutorService executor = Executors.newFixedThreadPool(3);
executor.submit(() -> {
    System.out.println("Thread using ExecutorService");
});
executor.shutdown();
âœ… Best for handling multiple tasks efficiently (used in production-level apps).

5. Using Callable with Future (if return value is needed)

ExecutorService executor = Executors.newSingleThreadExecutor();
Callable<String> task = () -> "Task Completed!";
Future<String> result = executor.submit(task);

System.out.println(result.get()); // waits and prints: Task Completed!
executor.shutdown();
âœ… Use this when your thread needs to return a result or throw an exception.

âœ… Summary Table:
| Method                | Can return result?       | Allows exception? | Flexible? | Common Usage             |
| --------------------- | ------------------------ | ----------------- | --------- | ------------------------ |
| `Thread` class        | âŒ No                     | âŒ No              | âŒ Less    | Simple threaded logic    |
| `Runnable` interface  | âŒ No                     | âŒ No              | âœ… Yes     | Lightweight tasks        |
| `Lambda` expression   | âŒ No                     | âŒ No              | âœ… Yes     | Short tasks, readability |
| `ExecutorService`     | âŒ (or âœ… with `Callable`) | âœ… Yes             | âœ… Very    | Thread pool tasks        |
| `Callable` + `Future` | âœ… Yes                    | âœ… Yes             | âœ… Yes     | When result is needed    |

